You gotta run.

544
00:25:06,123 --> 00:25:07,018
That's right.

545
00:25:08,621 --> 00:25:10,190
Ahem.

546
00:25:10,255 --> 00:25:12,016
Excuse me.

547
00:25:12,082 --> 00:25:14,067
What do you mean
we've gotta run?

548
00:25:14,131 --> 00:25:17,109
Well, we gotta pay
for this somehow.

549
00:25:17,173 --> 00:25:18,294
And I'm all out of cash.

550
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:19,768
So what are we supposed
to do about that?

551
00:25:19,833 --> 00:25:21,306
You're going to walk
out of here right now.

552
00:25:21,370 --> 00:25:22,267
You're not going to talk

553
00:25:22,331 --> 00:25:23,228
To your buddy
on the door,

554
00:25:23,292 --> 00:25:23,773
And you're going
to go get some.

555
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:27,839
And if you're
not back here by 5:30

556
00:25:27,904 --> 00:25:30,979
With say, 300 bucks,

557
00:25:31,044 --> 00:25:34,374
Well, you know
what they say.

558
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:35,752
Never pick a fight
with someone

559
00:25:35,817 --> 00:25:36,808
Who's got
nothing to lose.

560
00:25:41,135 --> 00:25:42,510
[cell phone beeps]

561
00:25:42,575 --> 00:25:43,857
Run along.

562
00:25:45,554 --> 00:25:47,636
[keypad beeping]

563
00:25:51,865 --> 00:25:53,274
That's good.

564
00:25:53,338 --> 00:25:54,554
Who you calling?
Kristin.

565
00:25:54,621 --> 00:25:55,771
That designer
I met last month.

566
00:25:55,837 --> 00:25:57,437
Who?
Kristin.

567
00:25:57,503 --> 00:25:58,463
Will you ever listen
to anything I say?

568
00:25:58,528 --> 00:25:59,807
She's 4 blocks
from here.

569
00:25:59,872 --> 00:26:01,089
Voicemail.
No answer.

570
00:26:01,155 --> 00:26:02,050
There's gotta be
someone else

571
00:26:02,116 --> 00:26:03,140
We know around here.

572
00:26:03,204 --> 00:26:04,101
We don't know anyone
on this side of town.

573
00:26:04,165 --> 00:26:05,413
How does he know
about our lives?

574
00:26:05,478 --> 00:26:06,374
What have we done
to him?

575
00:26:06,439 --> 00:26:07,528
We haven't
done anything, babe.

576
00:26:07,593 --> 00:26:09,258
Ok? He's just crazy.
That's what it is.

577
00:26:09,322 --> 00:26:10,603
Do you know him from work?
Tell me.

578
00:26:10,668 --> 00:26:11,981
Is it from accounts?
Somebody you pissed off?

579
00:26:12,045 --> 00:26:13,678
No. What enough
that he'd take our kid?

580
00:26:13,775 --> 00:26:15,438
I don't think so.
No way.

581
00:26:15,536 --> 00:26:16,752
We've only got 15 minutes.

582
00:26:16,817 --> 00:26:18,355
Oh, god.
Listen to me.

583
00:26:18,419 --> 00:26:20,213
Listen to me.
He's got to get the money.

584
00:26:20,278 --> 00:26:22,935
Please. Uh,
this is important. It's--

585
00:26:23,001 --> 00:26:23,929
Neil!

586
00:26:25,658 --> 00:26:26,714
Neil!

587
00:26:26,779 --> 00:26:28,413
We really need your help.

588
00:26:28,478 --> 00:26:29,470
Please listen to us.

589
00:26:29,535 --> 00:26:31,840
My name is Neil Randall.
And, uh,

590
00:26:31,906 --> 00:26:33,505
This is my card.
This is my wife.

591
00:26:33,571 --> 00:26:35,236
Ok, we need--
we need money.

592
00:26:35,301 --> 00:26:36,227
We're not begging.

593
00:26:36,292 --> 00:26:37,285
Ok, if you could just--

594
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:38,950
Oh, I'm late
for a meeting.

595
00:26:39,015 --> 00:26:40,906
No. No, you get back.

596
00:26:40,971 --> 00:26:42,442
Our daughter could--

597
00:26:42,572 --> 00:26:43,980
No, don't!

598
00:26:44,046 --> 00:26:46,126
Our daughter could die
if you don't help us.

599
00:26:47,312 --> 00:26:48,657
If you don't take
your hands off of me

600
00:26:48,721 --> 00:26:49,650
In the next 2 seconds--

601
00:26:49,715 --> 00:26:51,124
Neil, let him go.
Let's go.

602
00:26:51,189 --> 00:26:52,854
I have an idea.
I have an idea!

603
00:26:58,138 --> 00:26:59,068
[bell rings]

604
00:26:59,133 --> 00:27:01,182
[panting]
'Scuse me. 'Scuse me.

605
00:27:01,247 --> 00:27:02,655
We need to sell
this bracelet.

606
00:27:02,721 --> 00:27:04,834
[both panting]

607
00:27:04,899 --> 00:27:06,178
I paid 2 grand for that.

608
00:27:06,244 --> 00:27:07,138
We only
need 300.

609
00:27:07,204 --> 00:27:07,812
Yeah.
Ok.

610
00:27:09,895 --> 00:27:11,464
Come on. We gotta go.

611
00:27:13,418 --> 00:27:15,052
It's a fake.
Give you 20 bucks.

612
00:27:16,878 --> 00:27:18,574
What?
It's not a fake.

613
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,887
Are you kidding me?

614
00:27:19,953 --> 00:27:20,914
Baby, I paid
2 grand for it, ok?

615
00:27:20,979 --> 00:27:22,579
Stop.
[shopkeeper laughs]

616
00:27:22,644 --> 00:27:24,084
Shopkeeper:
I was kidding. Kidding.

617
00:27:24,181 --> 00:27:25,750
I'll give you 200, ok?

618
00:27:25,816 --> 00:27:28,216
Funny. 300.

619
00:27:28,281 --> 00:27:29,466
Oh, forget it.

620
00:27:32,190 --> 00:27:34,784
Yeah. Well, there's
just one little thing.

621
00:27:36,611 --> 00:27:38,915
I can't forget it.

622
00:27:38,980 --> 00:27:41,125
300. Now.

623
00:27:41,191 --> 00:27:43,977
[metal screeching]

624
00:27:44,042 --> 00:27:45,321
Neil:
come on. We got 2 minutes.

625
00:27:48,205 --> 00:27:49,358
This way.

626
00:27:49,422 --> 00:27:50,319
[horn honks]
aah!

627
00:27:50,383 --> 00:27:51,087
[horn honks]

628
00:27:54,260 --> 00:27:55,540
[indistinct chatter]

629
00:27:55,605 --> 00:27:56,853
[glasses clink]

630
00:28:03,484 --> 00:28:05,245
Where'd he go?
S-sir?

631
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,463
Where did he go?

632
00:28:06,528 --> 00:28:07,553
He was sitting
right there.

633
00:28:07,617 --> 00:28:09,345
I--I'm sorry, sir.
I didn't see, um...

634
00:28:09,410 --> 00:28:11,363
The man, he was
sitting right there.

635
00:28:11,428 --> 00:28:12,453
Uh, I'm sorry, I--

636
00:28:12,518 --> 00:28:13,478
Come on.
You must have!

637
00:28:13,542 --> 00:28:14,279
Hey.

638
00:28:16,586 --> 00:28:18,602
Dead on time.

639
00:28:20,718 --> 00:28:22,511
Now this place
ain't bad.

640
00:28:22,576 --> 00:28:24,721
I might bring
the good wife here, huh?

641
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:27,348
Settle this up,
would you, Neil?

642
00:28:27,413 --> 00:28:29,142
'Scuse us.

643
00:28:34,331 --> 00:28:35,869
So you got it?
Yeah.

644
00:28:35,934 --> 00:28:37,214
Quite
a performance.

645
00:28:37,279 --> 00:28:39,072
Let's see if you can
get to south frank

646
00:28:39,136 --> 00:28:40,160
Within 20 from here.

647
00:28:40,226 --> 00:28:41,730
I need this
delivered in person.

648
00:28:41,796 --> 00:28:42,787
What's this?
What's going on?

649
00:28:42,853 --> 00:28:43,973
Go and check the station
after it's done.

650
00:28:44,037 --> 00:28:45,606
Just a little errand
for Abby, Neil.

651
00:28:45,671 --> 00:28:46,567
Calm down.

652
00:28:46,632 --> 00:28:48,170
What is it?
I don't know.

653
00:28:48,235 --> 00:28:50,570
[indistinct]
easy, hey.

654
00:28:50,636 --> 00:28:52,300
I want to get to know you
a little better.

655
00:28:52,366 --> 00:28:53,775
We might have something
in common--

656
00:28:53,840 --> 00:28:54,960
For Christ's sake.

657
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:56,176
It's all right.
Neil.

658
00:28:56,242 --> 00:28:57,939
I can do it.

659
00:28:58,003 --> 00:28:59,379
I can deliver
a letter, ok?

660
00:29:00,726 --> 00:29:03,032
Ok, ok. You go.

661
00:29:03,128 --> 00:29:04,120
Take care, ok?

662
00:29:09,407 --> 00:29:11,808
You're not worried,
are you?

663
00:29:11,873 --> 00:29:13,058
She might see a cop.

664
00:29:13,122 --> 00:29:15,011
Start getting ideas.

665
00:29:15,077 --> 00:29:15,652
No, she'll do it.

666
00:29:17,895 --> 00:29:19,464
[gasps]

667
00:29:19,529 --> 00:29:20,393
Uhh.
Abby!

668
00:29:20,457 --> 00:29:22,155
Wait. Leave it.
Leave it.

669
00:29:22,220 --> 00:29:23,468
You son of a bitch!

670
00:29:23,534 --> 00:29:25,198
Just leave it, ok?

671
00:29:25,262 --> 00:29:26,735
All right?

672
00:29:26,801 --> 00:29:29,650
Anger's good, Neil.

673
00:29:29,714 --> 00:29:31,476
Come on.

674
00:29:31,540 --> 00:29:32,726
Come on. Let's go.

675
00:29:32,791 --> 00:29:33,879
Let's go.

676
00:29:37,692 --> 00:29:39,643
Boy: Hey!

677
00:29:41,342 --> 00:29:42,047
Hey!

678
00:29:45,443 --> 00:29:46,371
Hey.

679
00:29:51,081 --> 00:29:53,066
One word
and your daughter's dead.

680
00:29:55,149 --> 00:29:55,949
Hey.
Dad.

681
00:29:58,033 --> 00:30:00,081
It's good to see you, son.
How are you?

682
00:30:00,146 --> 00:30:01,425
What are you
doing here?

683
00:30:01,490 --> 00:30:03,347
Uh, well, I just, uh,

684
00:30:03,412 --> 00:30:05,110
Had to come in for work,

685
00:30:05,174 --> 00:30:06,583
And, uh,

686
00:30:06,648 --> 00:30:07,704
Well, what about you?

687
00:30:07,769 --> 00:30:08,634
I mean, I wouldn't
expect to see you

688
00:30:08,730 --> 00:30:09,595
On the Westside.

689
00:30:09,691 --> 00:30:10,682
Kory, that girl

690
00:30:10,748 --> 00:30:11,933
I met
in social studies.

691
00:30:11,997 --> 00:30:14,047
She lives just
down the street, so.

692
00:30:14,112 --> 00:30:15,199
Good. [chuckles]

693
00:30:15,266 --> 00:30:16,865
Good.

694
00:30:18,468 --> 00:30:20,101
Is, uh,
everything ok?

695
00:30:20,167 --> 00:30:21,413
Yeah, I'm fine.

696
00:30:21,479 --> 00:30:24,169
Oh, just work, job.

697
00:30:24,234 --> 00:30:25,835
I got a lot on my mind
and stuff.

698
00:30:25,900 --> 00:30:28,237
Listen, we gotta run.

699
00:30:28,302 --> 00:30:29,423
I'll catch you
later on, ok?

700
00:30:29,584 --> 00:30:30,670
Yeah, sure.

701
00:30:30,737 --> 00:30:35,156
Could you--
uh, use a ride, or...

702
00:30:35,220 --> 00:30:36,885
Yeah.
Neil.

703
00:30:36,950 --> 00:30:39,416
Have you forgotten
something?

704
00:30:39,481 --> 00:30:41,274
If you're late?

705
00:30:41,338 --> 00:30:43,485
Huh?

706
00:30:43,550 --> 00:30:44,925
Your wife'll kill you.

707
00:30:44,990 --> 00:30:46,272
Yeah, I forgot.

708
00:30:47,457 --> 00:30:48,610
I'm sorry, son.
We're pushed for time.

709
00:30:48,674 --> 00:30:50,499
I'll talk
to you later, ok?

710
00:30:50,565 --> 00:30:51,492
Sure.

711
00:31:00,399 --> 00:31:02,030
[engine starts]

712
00:31:18,464 --> 00:31:20,898
So you got
a child of your own

713
00:31:20,964 --> 00:31:22,019
And you put us
through this.

714
00:31:24,807 --> 00:31:26,054
What's he going to think
of the two of you

715
00:31:26,121 --> 00:31:26,855
When this comes out?

716
00:31:30,060 --> 00:31:31,598
[telephones ringing]

717
00:31:37,108 --> 00:31:38,324
Have you thought
about that?

718
00:31:41,112 --> 00:31:42,294
[engine accelerates]

719
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:43,128
[brakes squeal]

720
00:31:48,927 --> 00:31:51,361
Hey, what's he going
to think, huh?

721
00:31:51,426 --> 00:31:52,898
Tell me.

722
00:31:52,962 --> 00:31:54,404
Come on.

723
00:31:54,468 --> 00:31:55,652
What's he going to think?

724
00:31:55,718 --> 00:31:57,158
What's he going
to tell Kory

725
00:31:57,223 --> 00:31:58,696
When mom and dad
are on the evening news?

726
00:31:58,761 --> 00:32:00,522
Have you thought
about that?

727
00:32:00,587 --> 00:32:01,996
Well, have you?

728
00:32:06,801 --> 00:32:08,114
What the hell
are you doing?!

729
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:11,958
[panting and grunting]

730
00:32:15,290 --> 00:32:16,570
Uhh.

731
00:32:16,634 --> 00:32:18,908
[unwrapping plastic]

732
00:32:18,973 --> 00:32:20,190
[flicks lighter]

733
00:32:20,255 --> 00:32:21,599
How's everything
going at work?

734
00:32:21,665 --> 00:32:23,040
[gasping]

735
00:32:28,231 --> 00:32:30,472
I hear advertising's
a cutthroat business.

736
00:32:30,536 --> 00:32:31,786
A lot of pressure.

737
00:32:35,438 --> 00:32:37,103
Is that why you screw up
so many people's lives?

738
00:32:37,167 --> 00:32:39,153
What are you talking about?

739
00:32:40,531 --> 00:32:41,075
Recognize that place?

740
00:32:43,253 --> 00:32:45,109
Fifth floor.
Straight ahead.

741
00:32:46,584 --> 00:32:48,666
That's the head office
of Magris industries.

742
00:32:48,731 --> 00:32:51,068
You've heard of them?

743
00:32:51,133 --> 00:32:53,342
Of course you have.

744
00:32:53,407 --> 00:32:54,400
And with this

745
00:32:54,464 --> 00:32:55,809
Million dollar launch
coming up,

746
00:32:55,873 --> 00:32:57,027
I'm sure
this is something

747
00:32:57,091 --> 00:32:59,012
You'd want to keep
under wraps.

748
00:32:59,077 --> 00:33:00,678
What do you get for
hacking into

749
00:33:00,743 --> 00:33:02,600
Corporate information
these days?

750
00:33:03,817 --> 00:33:04,937
Where'd you get this?

751
00:33:05,003 --> 00:33:07,757
Ah, don't panic.
It's only a copy.

752
00:33:09,744 --> 00:33:11,473
Abby has the original.

753
00:33:16,183 --> 00:33:17,207
Yeah,
it's all down there

754
00:33:17,271 --> 00:33:18,168
In black and white.

755
00:33:18,232 --> 00:33:19,865
Times, places.

756
00:33:19,931 --> 00:33:22,268
How you bought your way
into getting that account.

757
00:33:22,332 --> 00:33:23,964
What would
the competition do

758
00:33:24,030 --> 00:33:25,855
With something like that?

759
00:33:25,919 --> 00:33:28,578
Your company's reputation
will be ruined.

760
00:33:28,643 --> 00:33:29,539
But Karl
won't blame you, Neil.

761
00:33:32,231 --> 00:33:32,935
Will he?

762
00:33:35,785 --> 00:33:37,418
Well, Mr. Carver's
due back any minute,

763
00:33:37,484 --> 00:33:38,989
But I can give it
to him for you.

764
00:33:39,054 --> 00:33:40,206
No, it's ok.

765
00:33:40,271 --> 00:33:41,423
I've got to really give it
to him myself, thank you.

766
00:33:41,489 --> 00:33:42,481
Sure. Have a seat.

767
00:33:53,212 --> 00:33:54,747
You just want to destroy
everything we've got,

768
00:33:54,812 --> 00:33:55,772
Don't you?

769
00:33:55,838 --> 00:33:57,920
Look, I don't want
to destroy you, Neil.

770
00:33:57,984 --> 00:33:59,842
I'll prove it.

771
00:33:59,906 --> 00:34:01,315
I'll give you one shot.

772
00:34:01,379 --> 00:34:03,365
[cell phone beeps]

773
00:34:03,431 --> 00:34:04,295
Stop her.

774
00:34:04,359 --> 00:34:04,902
You serious?

775
00:34:04,966 --> 00:34:06,376
Stop her.

776
00:34:12,270 --> 00:34:13,744
[grunts]

777
00:34:13,809 --> 00:34:16,114
Uhh. Come on. Come on.
Shit!

778
00:34:18,324 --> 00:34:20,887
[cell phone beeps]

779
00:34:20,951 --> 00:34:23,514
[ring]

780
00:34:23,578 --> 00:34:25,562
[cell phone beeps]

781
00:34:25,755 --> 00:34:27,101
Hello?

782
00:34:27,166 --> 00:34:28,285
Abby? It's--

783
00:34:28,350 --> 00:34:30,207
It's Neil.

784
00:34:30,272 --> 00:34:32,931
Abby, don't hand over
that envelope.

785
00:34:32,995 --> 00:34:34,660
What?
Look,

786
00:34:34,725 --> 00:34:35,973
I--I don't have time
to explain.

787
00:34:36,038 --> 00:34:37,542
Just walk out
of the office, ok?

788
00:34:37,607 --> 00:34:39,594
We have to do
what he says, Neil.

789
00:34:39,659 --> 00:34:40,747
Think about Sophie.

790
00:34:40,812 --> 00:34:42,604
Get out of there,
Abby, please.

791
00:34:42,669 --> 00:34:44,270
No, listen to me.
We have to do what he said.

792
00:34:44,335 --> 00:34:45,391
Get out of there!

793
00:34:45,456 --> 00:34:46,447
Look, he says
it's all right.

794
00:34:46,512 --> 00:34:47,664
All right.

795
00:34:47,730 --> 00:34:48,818
Time's up.

796
00:35:03,201 --> 00:35:05,059
Oh, no. Abby, no!

797
00:35:10,506 --> 00:35:12,041
Excuse me.
Are you Mr. Carver?

798
00:35:12,106 --> 00:35:14,924
No! Abby,
for Christ's sake, no!

799
00:35:17,745 --> 00:35:19,153
No! Don't!

800
00:35:19,217 --> 00:35:21,651
Abby, for Christ's sake!
I said don't!

801
00:35:25,689 --> 00:35:26,359
Shit!

802
00:35:41,513 --> 00:35:43,594
Go on.

803
00:35:43,658 --> 00:35:44,587
You know
you're dying for one.

804
00:35:47,182 --> 00:35:48,814
Been thinking
about something you said

805
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:49,391
In that restaurant.

806
00:35:51,635 --> 00:35:52,754
Do you know what it was?

807
00:35:55,063 --> 00:35:58,296
"I'm Mr. Randall,"
you said.

808
00:35:58,361 --> 00:35:59,257
Maybe it's just me,

809
00:35:59,322 --> 00:36:00,506
But there's
something about you,

810
00:36:00,572 --> 00:36:01,467
Or anyone,

811
00:36:01,533 --> 00:36:02,716
Calling themselves mister

812
00:36:02,781 --> 00:36:04,286
That makes me feel
