00:49:35,083 --> 00:49:36,140
Why don't you
have a scotch

1080
00:49:36,205 --> 00:49:37,966
While you figure it out?

1081
00:49:39,121 --> 00:49:40,017
Neil!

1082
00:49:40,082 --> 00:49:41,426
Tell me where,
for Christ's sake!

1083
00:49:41,491 --> 00:49:43,027
Be where?

1084
00:49:43,188 --> 00:49:44,692
Prick!

1085
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:48,024
[door shuts]

1086
00:49:52,734 --> 00:49:54,398
Come on. Hurry up.

1087
00:49:54,463 --> 00:49:55,263
Unh!

1088
00:50:01,672 --> 00:50:02,438
Come on!

1089
00:50:05,386 --> 00:50:07,243
[distant siren blares]

1090
00:50:33,384 --> 00:50:35,719
[siren blares]

1091
00:50:35,784 --> 00:50:38,154
[indistinct chatter]

1092
00:50:48,951 --> 00:50:51,159
You just want
your life back.

1093
00:50:51,225 --> 00:50:53,467
What do you think?

1094
00:50:53,691 --> 00:50:55,132
Well,

1095
00:50:55,196 --> 00:50:56,828
Get out
of the car then.

1096
00:51:03,526 --> 00:51:04,517
Shit.

1097
00:51:12,558 --> 00:51:13,710
Hit the big time...

1098
00:51:26,492 --> 00:51:27,484
[panting]

1099
00:51:51,509 --> 00:51:52,661
Shit.

1100
00:51:52,727 --> 00:51:54,103
[elevator dings]

1101
00:51:56,857 --> 00:51:58,812
[bangs]

1102
00:52:01,118 --> 00:52:02,110
[button rattles]

1103
00:52:16,174 --> 00:52:17,839
[panting and grunting]

1104
00:52:20,530 --> 00:52:22,899
[footsteps clanging]

1105
00:52:32,703 --> 00:52:34,015
Oh, oh, shit.

1106
00:52:39,813 --> 00:52:41,543
[coughing]

1107
00:52:41,608 --> 00:52:44,426
[cell phone beeps]

1108
00:52:44,491 --> 00:52:46,891
[cell phone beeps]

1109
00:52:46,957 --> 00:52:47,884
Yeah?

1110
00:52:47,949 --> 00:52:49,870
Tom: Missing you
already.

1111
00:52:49,936 --> 00:52:52,593
I made it.
I'm at the clock tower.

1112
00:52:52,658 --> 00:52:54,099
Too late.

1113
00:52:54,164 --> 00:52:55,669
No, no, no,
I did what you asked.

1114
00:52:55,733 --> 00:52:57,847
I--I--I got here.

1115
00:52:57,911 --> 00:52:59,705
You're too late.

1116
00:52:59,770 --> 00:53:02,396
Jesus Christ.
What do you want from me?

1117
00:53:02,460 --> 00:53:03,709
It's not all bad.

1118
00:53:03,773 --> 00:53:04,829
I'll let you say
good-bye.

1119
00:53:04,894 --> 00:53:06,624
What? No, wait.

1120
00:53:09,572 --> 00:53:10,468
Abby: Neil? Neil?

1121
00:53:10,533 --> 00:53:11,429
Baby, listen.

1122
00:53:11,494 --> 00:53:12,390
Neil, listen, he's got--

1123
00:53:12,455 --> 00:53:14,407
Tom: Time's up.

1124
00:53:14,473 --> 00:53:16,746
W-where are you?

1125
00:53:16,811 --> 00:53:19,436
W-what are you
going to do?

1126
00:53:19,533 --> 00:53:21,358
Come and take
a look, Neil.

1127
00:53:23,601 --> 00:53:24,657
Where?

1128
00:53:24,755 --> 00:53:26,035
The edge, Neil.

1129
00:53:26,101 --> 00:53:28,564
Just step up to the edge
and look down.

1130
00:53:41,444 --> 00:53:42,692
Ok...Ok...

1131
00:53:42,757 --> 00:53:45,510
You're not scared,
are you?

1132
00:53:45,576 --> 00:53:46,632
A little bird
told me

1133
00:53:46,697 --> 00:53:48,457
You're not crazy
about heights.

1134
00:53:48,522 --> 00:53:49,546
I'm at the edge.

1135
00:53:49,611 --> 00:53:51,211
I'm at the goddamn edge!

1136
00:53:51,276 --> 00:53:53,231
Abby really wanted
one last look.

1137
00:53:53,295 --> 00:53:54,351
No, wait, wait.

1138
00:53:54,416 --> 00:53:55,472
But if you haven't
got the balls--

1139
00:53:55,538 --> 00:53:57,330
I can't even see you.

1140
00:53:57,395 --> 00:53:58,867
You're not
at the edge, Neil,

1141
00:53:58,933 --> 00:54:00,020
Or we'd see you.

1142
00:54:00,086 --> 00:54:01,046
I want
to see you standing.

1143
00:54:01,174 --> 00:54:02,167
Wait, wait!

1144
00:54:07,678 --> 00:54:09,567
Ok, ok, I--

1145
00:54:09,631 --> 00:54:11,425
I see you.

1146
00:54:11,490 --> 00:54:12,482
Stand up, Neil.

1147
00:54:12,547 --> 00:54:13,634
Abby: No...

1148
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:15,269
Get up.
No.

1149
00:54:15,334 --> 00:54:16,230
Neil, get up.

1150
00:54:16,295 --> 00:54:17,639
Please,
don't do this.

1151
00:54:17,705 --> 00:54:19,464
[Abby crying]

1152
00:54:19,530 --> 00:54:21,130
Be a real man
for once in your life.

1153
00:54:24,783 --> 00:54:25,904
Unh...

1154
00:54:37,211 --> 00:54:38,363
I'm here.

1155
00:54:38,429 --> 00:54:41,471
I'm...
[stammering]

1156
00:54:41,536 --> 00:54:43,071
Tell him to move back.
It's too dangerous.

1157
00:54:43,138 --> 00:54:44,033
I'm on the edge.

1158
00:54:44,099 --> 00:54:45,315
[indistinct]

1159
00:54:45,380 --> 00:54:47,012
Tell him to move back.
That's enough!

1160
00:54:47,078 --> 00:54:48,743
No, please,
he'll kill himself.

1161
00:54:48,839 --> 00:54:50,119
That's enough!
Listen to me!

1162
00:54:50,184 --> 00:54:52,041
[Tom grunts]
Abby: no!

1163
00:54:52,106 --> 00:54:53,259
Don't you touch her!

1164
00:54:53,323 --> 00:54:54,380
Get in the car.

1165
00:54:54,444 --> 00:54:55,820
[Abby weeping]

1166
00:54:55,887 --> 00:54:56,782
Stay in here.

1167
00:54:56,848 --> 00:54:57,679
Stay in there.

1168
00:54:57,744 --> 00:55:00,048
[sobbing]

1169
00:55:00,113 --> 00:55:03,091
Listen, it doesn't matter
that you were late.

1170
00:55:03,157 --> 00:55:04,918
I was going
to have her anyway.

1171
00:55:05,015 --> 00:55:07,321
Only she
doesn't know that yet.

1172
00:55:10,428 --> 00:55:11,357
Neil:
why are you doing this?

1173
00:55:11,422 --> 00:55:13,791
Why are you
doing this to me?

1174
00:55:13,856 --> 00:55:16,739
Why? Why...

1175
00:55:19,046 --> 00:55:20,582
Haven't you seen it yet?

1176
00:55:20,646 --> 00:55:22,023
Huh, Neil?

1177
00:55:22,088 --> 00:55:23,528
What are
you talking about?

1178
00:55:23,594 --> 00:55:24,681
The answer is up there.

1179
00:55:27,021 --> 00:55:28,302
Ah, it's right there.

1180
00:55:28,367 --> 00:55:30,736
Look around.

1181
00:55:30,801 --> 00:55:32,818
Where?

1182
00:55:32,882 --> 00:55:33,875
It's under your nose.

1183
00:55:33,939 --> 00:55:37,399
Come on, you want
to know why, don't you?

1184
00:55:42,300 --> 00:55:43,485
Aah!

1185
00:55:52,166 --> 00:55:54,279
What does it mean?

1186
00:55:54,344 --> 00:55:56,617
Tom: I'll tell you
what it means.

1187
00:55:56,683 --> 00:55:59,566
It means
stamping out a problem.

1188
00:55:59,631 --> 00:56:01,295
Crushing it.

1189
00:56:01,359 --> 00:56:03,473
So, now I've got
your daughter and your wife.

1190
00:56:05,619 --> 00:56:08,950
And you're just
a tiny dot in the sky

1191
00:56:09,016 --> 00:56:10,712
Worth nothing.

1192
00:56:10,777 --> 00:56:15,037
Please, no,
I'm begging you, don't.

1193
00:56:15,102 --> 00:56:18,047
And what exactly
am I going to do?

1194
00:56:18,112 --> 00:56:21,090
I'll leave that to
your imagination, Neil.

1195
00:56:21,186 --> 00:56:22,724
Don't you hang up!

1196
00:56:22,789 --> 00:56:23,812
Don't you hang up!

1197
00:56:23,877 --> 00:56:25,928
Sweet dreams.

1198
00:56:30,061 --> 00:56:32,365
A-Abby!

1199
00:56:32,430 --> 00:56:33,455
Abby!

1200
00:56:37,717 --> 00:56:39,221
[Neil sobbing]

1201
00:56:57,960 --> 00:56:59,625
[screams]

1202
00:57:01,292 --> 00:57:02,988
[thunder]

1203
00:57:05,808 --> 00:57:07,249
[sirens blaring]

1204
00:57:23,649 --> 00:57:25,251
[indistinct chatter]

1205
00:57:25,315 --> 00:57:26,884
Hey, whoa!
I need help.

1206
00:57:26,949 --> 00:57:28,005
Yeah, the line's
back there, sir.

1207
00:57:28,071 --> 00:57:29,415
No, this is
an emergency.

1208
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:32,075
My--my wife and child
have been kidnapped.

1209
00:57:32,140 --> 00:57:33,674
There's a psycho out there,

1210
00:57:33,740 --> 00:57:36,975
Ok, he--he's taken
my wife and my little girl.

1211
00:57:37,040 --> 00:57:38,928
You got my car,
he's driving my car.

1212
00:57:39,025 --> 00:57:40,242
He--it's a range rover,

1213
00:57:40,307 --> 00:57:43,765
"r"-"u", uh, 83--83 "a."

1214
00:57:43,829 --> 00:57:45,494
And there--he's got
a woman who's helping him.

1215
00:57:45,559 --> 00:57:46,616
She's--

1216
00:57:46,713 --> 00:57:48,089
Pretending
to be a sitter?

1217
00:57:48,155 --> 00:57:50,620
Randall, right?
Your name is Neil Randall?

1218
00:57:50,686 --> 00:57:51,646
Yeah.

1219
00:57:51,711 --> 00:57:53,694
I just spoke
to your wife.

1220
00:57:53,759 --> 00:57:55,713
She was here.
What?

1221
00:57:57,796 --> 00:57:58,789
W-wait, when?

1222
00:57:58,853 --> 00:58:00,518
About half
an hour ago.

1223
00:58:04,779 --> 00:58:05,772
You spoke--
you spoke to my wife?

1224
00:58:05,836 --> 00:58:07,085
Yeah.
She's ok?

1225
00:58:07,149 --> 00:58:08,365
She explained
the whole thing.

1226
00:58:08,431 --> 00:58:09,583
Ok.

1227
00:58:09,649 --> 00:58:10,865
She said that
you might show up

1228
00:58:10,930 --> 00:58:12,562
With this story.

1229
00:58:12,627 --> 00:58:13,618
At the state
you're in,

1230
00:58:13,683 --> 00:58:14,900
You'll try anything
to stop her.

1231
00:58:17,880 --> 00:58:19,449
Stop her doing what?

1232
00:58:19,515 --> 00:58:20,666
Leaving you.

1233
00:58:22,398 --> 00:58:25,631
No, you don't
understand.

1234
00:58:25,697 --> 00:58:27,841
No, she's
not leaving me.

1235
00:58:27,907 --> 00:58:29,796
No, he made her
say that.

1236
00:58:29,860 --> 00:58:31,333
Ok? He's got
the whole thing planned.

1237
00:58:31,399 --> 00:58:34,088
He's smart. Oh, he--
he's smart, all right.

1238
00:58:34,152 --> 00:58:36,426
He, uh--he's got
our daughter.

1239
00:58:36,490 --> 00:58:38,668
And he's made us--
forced us to do

1240
00:58:38,734 --> 00:58:40,879
Everything he says.

1241
00:58:40,943 --> 00:58:43,121
Look, I get it.
I know how you feel.

1242
00:58:43,187 --> 00:58:45,459
My wife left me
a year ago

1243
00:58:45,524 --> 00:58:47,798
I went a bit--[clicks]
crazy myself.

1244
00:58:47,862 --> 00:58:49,783
I'm not some
jealous husband, all right?

1245
00:58:49,848 --> 00:58:52,570
I'm the victim
of a crime!

1246
00:58:55,582 --> 00:58:58,400
Look,
you've been drinking.

1247
00:58:58,466 --> 00:58:59,266
I'm not drunk.

1248
00:59:01,027 --> 00:59:03,110
He did this to me.

1249
00:59:03,175 --> 00:59:04,517
Do yourself a favor.

1250
00:59:04,583 --> 00:59:07,113
Go home, sober up.

1251
00:59:07,178 --> 00:59:09,867
Try and accept it,
all right?

1252
00:59:09,932 --> 00:59:11,118
Nothing for me to do.

1253
00:59:11,182 --> 00:59:12,494
Can't help you.

1254
00:59:12,688 --> 00:59:13,968
All right?

1255
00:59:14,033 --> 00:59:15,057
Let's go,
I'll walk you out.

1256
00:59:15,122 --> 00:59:16,979
[panting]

1257
00:59:48,627 --> 00:59:50,132
[distant siren blaring]

1258
01:00:13,325 --> 01:00:14,541
[sighs]

1259
01:00:39,783 --> 01:00:41,032
[gasps]
[grunts]

1260
01:00:41,097 --> 01:00:42,954
It's all right. Oh!

1261
01:00:43,019 --> 01:00:44,010
Oh, baby.
It's ok!

1262
01:00:44,076 --> 01:00:45,067
It's ok.
Are you ok?

1263
01:00:45,133 --> 01:00:46,379
He didn't touch me.

1264
01:00:46,446 --> 01:00:47,437
You promise me?

1265
01:00:47,567 --> 01:00:48,494
Yes, I promise.

1266
01:00:55,831 --> 01:00:57,463
He made me lie
to that cop.

1267
01:00:57,529 --> 01:00:59,417
I thought you were going
to fall off the building.

1268
01:00:59,482 --> 01:01:01,532
I thought you
were going to die.

1269
01:01:01,596 --> 01:01:02,589
Oh, baby.

1270
01:01:02,654 --> 01:01:03,870
Oh, baby
I thought I'd lost you.

1271
01:01:03,935 --> 01:01:06,241
I thought--
[chokes]

1272
01:01:06,305 --> 01:01:07,328
I thought
I'd lost everything.

1273
01:01:07,395 --> 01:01:08,386
It's ok.

1274
01:01:08,452 --> 01:01:09,635
Remember that feeling!

1275
01:01:11,944 --> 01:01:13,639
'cause the next time
I tell you to do something

1276
01:01:13,705 --> 01:01:15,049
You're going to do it,
right?

1277
01:01:15,114 --> 01:01:16,779
[thunder]

1278
01:01:16,845 --> 01:01:18,733
Right, Mr. Randall?

1279
01:01:20,912 --> 01:01:23,026
Good, now we understand
each other.

1280
01:01:23,090 --> 01:01:24,466
Get in the back.

1281
01:01:36,608 --> 01:01:37,759
Abby: Why don't
we just do it?

1282
01:01:37,824 --> 01:01:39,137
Whatever it is.

1283
01:01:41,701 --> 01:01:42,693
Yeah.

1284
01:02:09,409 --> 01:02:10,752
I love you, Abby.

1285
01:02:12,611 --> 01:02:13,828
You know that, right?

1286
01:02:19,434 --> 01:02:21,515
[whispers] look what it takes
for us to get this close.

1287
01:02:26,418 --> 01:02:29,588
You guess where
you're going yet?

1288
01:02:29,652 --> 01:02:32,150
Just tell us.

1289
01:02:32,216 --> 01:02:33,785
We're going where you
were going all along.

1290
01:02:36,540 --> 01:02:37,885
We're going
to meet the boss.

1291
01:02:39,934 --> 01:02:41,120
The top man.

1292
01:02:43,043 --> 01:02:43,939
Karl granger.

1293
01:02:52,492 --> 01:02:53,420
[whispers] I knew
it had something

1294
01:02:53,484 --> 01:02:54,605
To do with work.

1295
01:02:56,816 --> 01:02:59,282
Maybe.

1296
01:02:59,346 --> 01:03:02,453
Jesus. I don't know
anything, anymore.

1297
01:03:04,920 --> 01:03:06,393
Home sweet home.

1298
01:03:18,695 --> 01:03:20,550
[gears shift]

1299
01:03:20,616 --> 01:03:21,576
[keys click
and engine shuts off]

1300
01:03:28,369 --> 01:03:30,096
You first, now.

1301
01:03:30,161 --> 01:03:31,442
Just ease the way.

1302
01:03:34,038 --> 01:03:35,799
What do I tell him?

1303
01:03:35,863 --> 01:03:38,040
Just tell him the truth.

1304
01:03:40,123 --> 01:03:41,116
Get out.

1305
01:03:41,180 --> 01:03:42,686
[whispers]
just do it.

1306
01:03:46,371 --> 01:03:47,587
[door opens]

1307
01:03:47,651 --> 01:03:49,093
[frogs croaking]

1308
01:03:51,398 --> 01:03:52,454
[door shuts]

1309
01:04:07,735 --> 01:04:08,503
Hey, Neil.

1310
01:04:15,326 --> 01:04:16,928
There something
I forgot to ask you.

1311
01:04:16,992 --> 01:04:18,369
What?

1312
01:04:18,466 --> 01:04:20,196
How far
would you go?

1313
01:04:20,261 --> 01:04:22,822
What?

1314
01:04:22,887 --> 01:04:25,256
To save the things
most important to you.

1315
01:04:25,321 --> 01:04:26,345
How far?

1316
01:04:26,410 --> 01:04:28,427
I would do
whatever it takes

1317
01:04:28,493 --> 01:04:29,740
To protect my family.

1318
01:04:29,806 --> 01:04:31,727
Yeah, I can
understand that.

1319
01:04:31,792 --> 01:04:33,873
And that's
a great thing.

1320
01:04:33,937 --> 01:04:34,834
There's this
one last thing

1321
01:04:34,898 --> 01:04:35,635
I want you to do.

1322
01:04:44,028 --> 01:04:44,796
Go on.

1323
01:04:50,434 --> 01:04:52,131
I want you
to kill, Neil.

1324
01:04:54,117 --> 01:04:55,942
You wanted to know
what this was all about.

1325
01:04:56,008 --> 01:04:58,313
Well, this is it.

1326
01:05:01,166 --> 01:05:03,534
No. You are crazy.

1327
01:05:03,600 --> 01:05:04,783
I can't do that.

1328
01:05:04,848 --> 01:05:05,969
You don't have to.

1329
01:05:08,117 --> 01:05:10,390
But if you don't...

1330
01:05:10,454 --> 01:05:11,607
You'll never see
Sophie again.

1331
01:05:13,209 --> 01:05:15,097
Because believe
one thing,

1332
01:05:15,162 --> 01:05:18,909
I don't give a damn
what happens to me.

1333
01:05:20,802 --> 01:05:21,888
I can't--I can't--

1334
01:05:21,954 --> 01:05:23,266
Neil, there's
no debate here, ok?

1335
01:05:23,331 --> 01:05:24,227
There's one person
in that house

1336
01:05:24,292 --> 01:05:25,252
And if they're not dead

1337
01:05:25,317 --> 01:05:26,726
In the next 10 minutes,

1338
01:05:26,790 --> 01:05:27,463
Someone else will be.

1339
01:05:32,972 --> 01:05:35,567
Have you forgotten
that feeling already?

1340
01:05:37,394 --> 01:05:38,610
[scoffs]

1341
01:05:38,738 --> 01:05:39,827
10 minutes.

1342
01:05:47,164 --> 01:05:48,699
[exhales]

1343
01:06:17,049 --> 01:06:18,618
[door creaks]

1344
01:06:29,446 --> 01:06:30,918
[creaks and shuts]

1345
01:07:16,277 --> 01:07:17,525
