01:21:51,714 --> 01:21:53,411
Oh, Neil.

1617
01:21:55,399 --> 01:21:57,190
She never left
the house.

1618
01:22:02,669 --> 01:22:03,725
[bangs]

1619
01:22:06,545 --> 01:22:09,716
She had a nice day--

1620
01:22:09,780 --> 01:22:10,548
With a lovely sitter.

1621
01:22:12,407 --> 01:22:14,681
I made sure
that I got the best.

1622
01:22:14,745 --> 01:22:16,603
Only the best.

1623
01:22:16,667 --> 01:22:18,492
You set me up.

1624
01:22:18,558 --> 01:22:21,056
You set me up
from the start.

1625
01:22:21,120 --> 01:22:22,657
Little old me.

1626
01:22:24,291 --> 01:22:25,347
Can you believe it?

1627
01:22:29,961 --> 01:22:31,370
And you...

1628
01:22:31,434 --> 01:22:33,131
And you put me
through all of that?

1629
01:22:33,195 --> 01:22:34,348
How about this, Neil?

1630
01:22:34,412 --> 01:22:36,398
How about weeks
and months of knowing

1631
01:22:36,464 --> 01:22:38,416
You're not good enough?
Try that!

1632
01:22:40,787 --> 01:22:41,781
Abby!

1633
01:22:43,350 --> 01:22:46,040
It didn't
mean anything!

1634
01:22:46,104 --> 01:22:47,321
You gotta
believe me.

1635
01:22:47,387 --> 01:22:49,595
I do believe you.

1636
01:22:49,661 --> 01:22:52,318
I believe you.

1637
01:22:52,383 --> 01:22:55,008
But it meant
something to me.

1638
01:22:55,074 --> 01:22:56,803
And it meant
something to him.

1639
01:22:56,867 --> 01:22:59,205
Enough that you
would let him destroy

1640
01:22:59,271 --> 01:23:01,287
Every cent
we've worked for?

1641
01:23:01,353 --> 01:23:02,505
No, Neil.
Not every cent.

1642
01:23:14,902 --> 01:23:18,424
So, you just ruined
my career.

1643
01:23:18,650 --> 01:23:19,674
Did I?

1644
01:23:19,738 --> 01:23:21,276
Yes, I saw you
do that one, Abby.

1645
01:23:21,341 --> 01:23:23,166
And what
did you see, Neil?

1646
01:23:34,634 --> 01:23:36,137
None of it happened.

1647
01:23:36,204 --> 01:23:38,700
So you got it?
Yeah.

1648
01:23:38,765 --> 01:23:40,111
Quite a performance.

1649
01:23:50,649 --> 01:23:52,506
I found you out, Neil.

1650
01:23:52,572 --> 01:23:54,012
Just like I did
in Denver.

1651
01:23:57,920 --> 01:24:00,258
I have been
in so much pain.

1652
01:24:02,759 --> 01:24:04,487
Do you know
how that feels?

1653
01:24:06,666 --> 01:24:10,380
Watching you
sleep at night,

1654
01:24:10,446 --> 01:24:12,207
Watching you dream.

1655
01:24:14,065 --> 01:24:15,633
And knowing that
she watches you, too.

1656
01:24:20,664 --> 01:24:22,617
[sighs]

1657
01:24:22,747 --> 01:24:23,739
I'm done.

1658
01:24:25,629 --> 01:24:27,582
I get you.
I understand you.

1659
01:24:29,761 --> 01:24:30,849
But I don't want you.

1660
01:24:33,958 --> 01:24:35,494
Look, you still have
everything.

1661
01:24:35,558 --> 01:24:37,096
You still have
your house,

1662
01:24:37,161 --> 01:24:38,184
You still have
your career,

1663
01:24:38,249 --> 01:24:39,178
You'll always have
Sophie.

1664
01:24:39,242 --> 01:24:41,100
Everything's exactly
as it was.

1665
01:24:44,207 --> 01:24:46,193
Except for one thing.

1666
01:24:47,954 --> 01:24:49,652
Who breaks a butterfly
on a wheel?

1667
01:24:52,793 --> 01:24:53,816
I do, Neil.

1668
01:24:58,558 --> 01:25:00,255
I just wanted
to share those feelings

1669
01:25:00,320 --> 01:25:02,658
With you, if only
for a few hours.

1670
01:25:02,722 --> 01:25:06,501
Despair, loss,

1671
01:25:06,565 --> 01:25:09,320
Abandonment,

1672
01:25:09,385 --> 01:25:10,986
Betrayal.

1673
01:25:13,388 --> 01:25:14,765
Are they there, Neil?

1674
01:25:17,744 --> 01:25:18,994
Are they, baby?

1675
01:25:22,839 --> 01:25:24,022
Are they?

